# Internal project docs (plans, specs)
# Per-subdir excludes (NOT a blanket `.project/`) so that .project/stories/
# can stay TRACKED while everything else stays local-only. Git's gitignore
# spec disallows re-including files under a fully-excluded parent
# (https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore "It is not possible to re-include a
# file if a parent directory of that file is excluded"), which is why we
# enumerate each ignored subdir rather than using `.project/` + a negation.
.project/plans/
.project/specs/
.project/test-plans/
.project/test-reports/
.project/audit-findings-*.md
.project/ios-build-warnings-debt.md

# Claude Code agents (auto-generated)
.claude/agents/
.superpowers/
tests/web/.auth/

# Express API coverage
express-api/coverage/

# Firebase emulator debug logs
firebase-debug.log
firestore-debug.log
database-debug.log

# Deployed git SHA marker — written by deploy workflow on the server
express-api/.deployed-sha
journey-results/

# ─── SHY-0035 (2026-06-08): prevent re-commit of Allure-pattern CI artefacts ───
# Historical audit (`.project/audit/repo-size-audit-2026-06-08.md`) found 6
# top-level directories totalling ~42 GiB ever-committed (12.74 GiB pack)
# matching the Allure-report tree (`<dir>/pr/<n>/`, `<dir>/deploy/`,
# `<dir>/latest/`, `data/attachments/<hex>.zip`, `history/*-trend.json`).
# All currently have 0 files tracked but blobs persist in `.git/`. These
# rules prevent any future regression. Each entry is `/`-anchored at repo
# root so it doesn't shadow legitimate nested directories with the same
# name.
/data/
/playwright/pr/
/playwright/deploy/
/playwright/latest/
# Widened from `/express/pr/` (architect Suggestion 2026-06-08) — the
# Allure variant could emit `express/deploy/` or `express/latest/` too;
# `/express-api/` is the actual tracked source dir, distinct path.
/express/
/history/
# Same widening rationale — block all `kotlin/` subpaths at root.
/kotlin/
/android-e2e/

# Compiled mobile bundles — never commit; use the deploy workflow for
# Play Store / TestFlight uploads. The existing `**/build` entry covers
# generated `.apk`/`.aab` under `app/build/`, but explicit extension
# blocks catch any rogue copy made outside the build dir.
*.apk
*.aab
*.ipa

# Reject `.zip` blanket-style — every large historical blob in the
# 2026-06-08 audit was an Allure attachment `.zip`. If a future
# legitimate small `.zip` needs to be tracked (e.g. a font bundle),
# add an explicit `!path/to/legit.zip` negation here. Verify nothing
# legitimate is currently tracked via `git ls-files '*.zip'`.
*.zip
